Anonymous Tue 09 Apr 2019 04:33:14 No.22393494 Report
Quoted By:
>>22392205
I'm with >>22392471
Isekai stories really downplay that aspect of the genre, reducing it to more a side-element or pointless deus ex machina with no real bearing on the story in any meaningful way. The phenomenon itself is just shelved in lieu of what are usually just slice-of-life plots; the protags never really seem to question why they're there, how it happened, etc. A great deal of the story could revolve around trying to find an explanation for just what the fuck is going on. It's a strange way to make the character relatable for easy self-insertion. Besides, working the mystery of the isekai into the plot is where you can flex your creative muscle. It should present an opportunity for interesting plot and worldbuilding.
